VICIS, Inc. | Company Profile | angelMD



For InvestorsFor StartupsAbout UsBlogLog InSign upFor InvestorsFor StartupsAbout UsBlogLog InSign upClosePlease login or register to proceedYou have to login or register first to proceed.Register LoginSelect Your Account TypeBrowse the companies and invest as a physicianPhysicianRegister your startup to be listed on angelMD. Applying for funding is optional.StartupIf you are a physician and you want to register your medical startup, start by registering your startup. We will follow up to provide your investing credentials separately.Please crop the photoDoneCancelVICIS, Inc.VICIS, Inc. is developing a novel helmet technology to reduce risk of from head impacts, beginning with a football helmet.1of8 The Story:
 
Americans love football, but sports-related head injury is a widespread and increasing concern at all levels of the game.  Current football helmets do an effective job protecting against skull fracture, but they are not designed to reduce risk of traumatic brain injury. We’ve completely reimagined the football helmet, leveraging contributions thought-leading neurological surgeons and mechanical engineers.
The result is a product that is performing exceptionally well vs. current market-leading helmets in industry-standard impact tests.  These data, obtained from independent labs, suggest our helmet will significantly reduce impact forces. In addition to emphasizing safety, we have put great focus on fit, comfort, performance, and design. This will be a helmet players love to wear.
We are starting with football, but will expand into other contact sports.
We have attracted a world-class group of scientific and athletic advisors.  Our scientific advisors include three members of the NFL Head, Neck, and Spine Committee, including a co-Chair.  Our athletic advisors include two NFL Hall of Fame inductees and several Super Bowl champions.
We have raised $28M in grant and investment funding to date, including a grant from the NFL, GE, and Under Armour as part of the Head Health Challenge II initiative. Investors include Peregrine Group, Trilogy Equity Partners, AngelMD, W-Fund, Alliance of Angels, and a number of individual investors whose ranks include neurosurgeons, spine surgeons, attorneys, and current and former NFL players and coaches. We are currently filling a convertible note.
The helmet industry has been slow to innovate.  That needs to change.  We are driven to make a profound difference by making the game safer for athletes of all ages.  We welcome your support for our initiative.
 

 
 
